org.cip4.elk.alces.preprocessor.jdf
Class UrlResolvingPreprocessor

java.lang.Object
  org.cip4.elk.alces.preprocessor.jdf.UrlResolvingPreprocessor
All Implemented Interfaces:
JDFPreprocessor
public class UrlResolvingPreprocessor
extends java.lang.Object
implements JDFPreprocessor

A preprocessor that examines all //FileSpec/@URL attributes found in a JDF instance. If a FileSpec/@URL contains a relative URL (the URL has no scheme), then the URL is resolved against a base URL to create an absolute URL. The FileSpec/@URL is then updated with the new aboluste URL.

Author:
Claes Buckwalter (claes.buckwalter@agfa.com)

BASEURL_ATTR

public static final java.lang.String BASEURL_ATTR
Attribute for storing the new JobID in the context. If this preprocessor finds this attribute in the context it will use it as the new JobID.

preprocess

public org.cip4.jdflib.node.JDFNode preprocess(org.cip4.jdflib.node.JDFNode jdf,
                                               PreprocessorContext context)
                                        throws PreprocessorException
All relative URLs (URLs witout a scheme) are resolved against the base URL and replaced with the resolved absolute URL. If a URL cannot be resolved a warning is logged and the URL is skipped. If the PreprocessorContext contains the attribute BASEURL_ATTR it will override the base URL configured by the constructor.

public static org.cip4.jdflib.node.JDFNode resolveReferencedFiles(org.cip4.jdflib.node.JDFNode jdf,

All relative URLs (URLs without a scheme) are resolved against the base URL and replaced with the resolved URL. If a URL cannot be resolved a warning is logged and the URL is skipped.

Parameters:
